Ah--I had thought the original poster wanted code without tests for 
which tests could be written.  For code that currently has tests, 
there&#39;s always the Money sample that ships with JUnit itself.

As far as the Eclipse runner, I myself maintain suites by hand--for 
continuous integration and collaborators using Emacs, it&#39;s great to be 
able to run the tests simply from the command line.  I do, however, 
regularly use the JUnit shortcut for running a given class or method, 
and those are cool.

    David Saff

